text: Aglaia argentea is a species of plant in the family Meliaceae. It is a tree found in Australia, Brunei, India, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar, Papua New Guinea, the Philippines, the Solomon Islands, and Thailand. ==References== * argentea Category:Sapindales of Australia Category:Flora of tropical Asia Category:Least concern flora of Australia Category:Least concern biota of Queensland Category:Rare flora of Australia Category:Flora of Queensland Category:Nature Conservation Act rare biota Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
